notesStmt.note: Incipit of first work: Corpus humanum potest dividi vel ratione finis vel ratione ... (f. 1r).
A page of densely layered notes (f. 129v) includes phrases in English and the dates 1609 and 1636; notes on another page (f. 130v) refer to Scotland.

msContents.summary: Treatises on medicine, history, geometry, and optics.

msItem.title: Brevio descriptio anatomica corporis humani, f. 1r
Perutiles quedam observationes ex libro i pathologice, f. 25r

support.watermark: Pitcher with a tiara topped with a quatrefoil and crescent.

supportDesc.extent: 130 leaves : 183 x 144 (163 x 114) mm. bound to 181 x 150 mm

collation.p: Paper, 130; 1¹⁶( -2), 2-3¹⁶, 4⁸( -1), 5⁸, 6¹⁶, 7⁸, 8¹⁶, 9¹², 10⁸, 11¹²( -1), 12¹², 13¹²( -1), 14¹⁶( -1), 15-16⁸, 17⁸( -2), 18¹², 19¹⁶, 20¹²( -1), 21-22¹⁶, 23⁸( -1); [1-130]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary parchment; several leaves loose or detached.

origin.p: Written between 1644 and 1646, possibly in Aberdeen (f. 60r).

history.provenance: Former owners include: Robert William Duff (bookplate, inside upper cover); Jane Clerk Duff, 1858 (signature, inside upper cover).
